    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-19T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-19T09:00:00-05:00" n="658"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d658">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3831/141: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-19T09:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 19, 1935—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:25 a.m]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Reference to Legation’s despatch No. 565, March 12,<note n="17"
                        xml:id="d658fn17">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_650">p. 650</ref>.</note>
                    regarding trade agreement, and situation resulting from French representations.
                    I am planning to leave here March 21 and an indication of Department’s attitude
                    on this question as well as bank sale plan<note n="18" xml:id="d658fn18">See
                            <ref target="#pg_703">pp. 703</ref> ff.</note> would be helpful before
                    final interview with President noon tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
